# AEM After — Post-Deployment Verification

Verify an AEM component after deployment — walk dialog fields, create a test page, and save verification docs. Compare against baseline if `aem-before.md` exists.

## How to use

```
@AemAfter hero
@AemAfter starterkit
```

## Configuration

Read `.ai/config.yaml` for:
- `aem.component-path` — component definitions root
- `aem.resource-type-pattern` — resource type format
- `aem.author-url` — AEM author URL (defaults to `http://localhost:4502`)
- `aem.content-paths` — configured content paths

## Steps

### 1. Load baseline and plan

Read `<spec-dir>/aem-before.md` to get the baseline field list.
Read `<spec-dir>/implement.md` to get new field names and expected test values.

### 2. Walk the current dialog

Same procedure as AemBefore — walk all tabs, extract all fields.

### 3. Compare with baseline

If `aem-before.md` exists:
- **New fields:** in current but not in baseline
- **Removed fields:** in baseline but not in current
- **Changed fields:** same name but different type/label

### 4. Create demo page (if applicable)

1. Read `aem.demo-parent-path` from `.ai/config.yaml` (fall back to `<language-root>/demo`)
2. Create demo parent folder page if missing
3. Create demo page with the component
4. Configure demo data — search for an existing authored instance of the component via AEM MCP, extract its real properties, and copy them to the demo component. Only use mock values for fields with no real data found

### 5. Save verification

Write `<spec-dir>/aem-after.md`:

```markdown
# AEM Verification: <component-name>

**Component:** `<resource-type>`
**Verified:** <ISO date>

## Dialog Changes (vs baseline)

| Change | Field | Details |
|--------|-------|---------|
| ADDED | <name> | <type> — <label> |
| REMOVED | <name> | was: <type> |
| CHANGED | <name> | <what changed> |

## All Current Fields

### Tab: <tab-name>
| Field | Type | Label | Property |
|-------|------|-------|----------|
| ... | ... | ... | ... |

## Test Page

**URL:** [Open in Author](<author-url>/editor.html<path>.html)
**Status:** Created / Already existed / Skipped
```

## Rules

- **Config-driven** — read all paths from `.ai/config.yaml`
- **Compare if baseline exists** — highlight what changed
- **Create test page when possible** — verify end-to-end
- **Compact output** — structured summaries only
